Groups of friends mark target employers on the event map. An alumni panel discusses preparation for technical interviews, and workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom. As the day winds down, interview sign-up sheets fill with names, and students exit with tote bags and a stack of business cards as the dean expresses gratitude to recruiters and volunteers gather leftover brochures.

Consulting firms stack glossy case study booklets on high tables, and human resources teams jot notes on tablets as students introduce themselves, contributing to a collaborative atmosphere. Recruiters distribute tote bags filled with branded notebooks and pens. The engineering society sponsors a resume review table near the stage, and an aroma of coffee and catered snacks spreads from the lounge. Workshops on networking etiquette begin in the adjoining classroom. A startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, while volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures. Friends decompress on the quad, comparing which companies responded warmly.
